description._content: Catalog #: 09_01589 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Memorial photo of Lockheed P-38 aircraft signed by fifty-five flying personnel at Lockheed following Elwyn Gibbon's death. The memorial was presented to his wife Toni. Many famous names appear including Marshall Headle, Jimmy Mattern, Joe Towle, Tony LeVier, H.R. Salmon, Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Corporation Name: Lockheed Corporation Tags: Elwyn H.
